# Security and Supabase

See [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md) and [`docs/security/authorization-model.md`](../../docs/security/authorization-model.md).

- RLS + SECURITY DEFINER RPCs are the enforcement layer; UI hiding is not sufficient
- Verify `auth.uid()`, membership, location access, and role inside every sensitive RPC
- Do not drop legacy invite tables until new flow is verified and legacy rows are empty
- Do not apply migrations to production or run `supabase db push` / `migration repair` without approval
- Do not broadly revoke EXECUTE from advisor warnings alone — trace callers first
- Receipt confirmation: Owner/Manager only (current)

**Drift:** [`docs/status/production-drift.md`](../../docs/status/production-drift.md)
